  "description": "German entrepreneur who consolidated the contemporary online-pornography industry through Manwin (later MindGeek), acquired in 2010 with $362 million in secured debt at approximately 24% interest arranged through Colbeck Capital. Thylmann sold his stake in 2013 to a management group led by Bergmair, Antoon, and Tassillo. Profiled by *The New Yorker* in 2014 as 'the Zuckerberg of free porn.'",
